N1  - E26. Decision-Making And Storytelling. 
N1  - E27. The lesson used Apple's Siri to illustrate AI decision-making, demonstrating how Siri makes decisions like determining when to activate.. 
N1  - E28. A decision tree was introduced to the class, with the root node posing the question, "Is someone saying 'Hey Siri' or 'Oye Siri'?". 
N1  - E29. The exercise effectively visualized the decision-making process for the students, and the instructor drew a parallel between decision trees in AI and storytelling, referencing "Choose Your Own Adventure" stories.. 
N1  - E30. The instructor used seven images to inspire different story elements, crafting a two-layer decision tree to demonstrate how decision trees can map out narrative paths in a story, mirroring the decision-making process in AI (Jacob et al., 2018; Minsky, 2019).. 
