N1  - E32. The second strategy involved role-playing as an AI to model Programmability and Learning from Data, deepening students' understanding of how AI works.. 
N1  - E33. Students simulated the operations of a conversational agent, interacting with Siri and posing questions to deepen their understanding of how Siri knows what to answer to a prompt and how Siri learned so many languages.. 
N1  - E34. The activity introduced the concept of a database of answers linked to specific prompts, and students created their own databases and took on the role of a conversational agent, being "trained" on the database and subsequently "tested" on their knowledge.. 
